.TH KEYPRESS 1 "2025-02-17" "1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
keypress \- layout-aware X11 keyboard automation tool
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B keypress.py
[\fB\-h\fR]
[\fB\-c\fR \fICOMMAND\fR]
[\fB\-d\fR \fIDELAY\fR]
[\fB\-t\fR \fITYPING_DELAY\fR]
[\fB\-w\fR \fIWINDOW\fR]
[\fB\-n\fR]
[\fB\-e\fR]
[\fB\-\-debug\fR]
.I program
.RI [ script ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B keypress.py
is a keyboard automation tool that respects your system keyboard layout, unlike xdotool which uses hardcoded US keycodes. It properly handles multi-column keymaps, AltGr symbols, and provides both system-layout and emulator modes.

The tool was created to solve the problem of automating keyboard input on non-US layouts (Finnish, German, Swedish, etc.) where symbols like brackets and backslashes are in different keymap columns than US layouts expect.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Show help message and exit.
.TP
.BI \-c\  COMMAND \fR,\ \fB\-\-command\  COMMAND
Execute a single command. Can be repeated for multiple commands. If no script file is provided, at least one \fB\-c\fR option is required.
.TP
.BI \-d\  DELAY \fR,\ \fB\-\-delay\  DELAY
Startup delay in seconds before searching for the program window. Default: 2.0. Increase if window detection fails.
.TP
.BI \-t\  TYPING_DELAY \fR,\ \fB\-\-typing\-delay\  TYPING_DELAY
Delay between individual keystrokes in seconds. Default: 0.03 (30ms). Increase for slower typing, decrease for faster.
.TP
.BI \-w\  WINDOW \fR,\ \fB\-\-window\  WINDOW
Window name pattern to search for. Recommended for reliable window detection. The pattern is case-insensitive and matches partial names.
.TP
.B \-n, \-\-no\-wait
Exit immediately after executing the script instead of waiting for the program to exit. Useful for background processes.
.TP
.B \-e, \-\-emulator\-mode
Use hardcoded US keyboard layout instead of system layout. Required for emulators (DOSBox-X, VICE, MAME) that internally expect US keyboard layout.
.TP
.B \-\-debug
Enable debug output showing detected keyboard mapping. Displays which characters are cached and their keycodes/modifiers.
.SH POSITIONAL ARGUMENTS
.TP
.I program
Program to launch. If the program command contains arguments or spaces, enclose in quotes: "dosbox-x -c 'mount c ~/dos'".
.TP
.I script
Path to script file containing commands to execute. Optional if \fB\-c\fR is used.
.SH SCRIPT FILE FORMAT
Each line in the script file is typed followed by Enter, unless special commands are used.

.SS Regular Text
.nf
dir /p
echo "Hello"
path=c:\\dos
.fi

.SS Special Keys
Special keys are enclosed in angle brackets:
.nf
<Esc>              Escape key
<Tab>              Tab key
<Backspace>        Backspace
<Delete>           Delete key
<Return>           Enter/Return
<Space>            Space bar
<F1> ... <F12>     Function keys
<Up> <Down>        Arrow keys
<Left> <Right>
<Home> <End>       Navigation keys
<PageUp> <PageDown>
.fi

.SS Key Combinations
Use + to combine keys:
.nf
<Ctrl+c>           Ctrl+C (copy)
<Ctrl+v>           Ctrl+V (paste)
<Alt+F4>           Alt+F4 (close)
<Shift+Insert>     Shift+Insert
<Ctrl+Alt+Del>     Three-key combo
.fi

.SS Special Commands
.nf
<wait:2>           Wait 2 seconds
<wait:0.5>         Wait 500 milliseconds
<nowait>           Don't press Enter after previous line
# comment          Comment line (ignored)
.fi

.SS Complete Example
.nf
# Wait for app to start
<wait:2>

# Type username
admin
<Tab>

# Type password
secret123
<Return>

# Wait for login
<wait:1>

# Open file
<Ctrl+o>
test.txt
<Return>
.fi

.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Normal Applications
Automate text editor with system keyboard layout:
.nf
keypress.py "leafpad" script.txt -w leafpad
keypress.py "gedit" commands.txt -w gedit -d 3
.fi

.SS Emulators
Automate DOSBox with US layout (required):
.nf
keypress.py "dosbox-x" dos.txt -w DOSBox --emulator-mode
keypress.py "vice" game.txt -w VICE -e -d 5
.fi

.SS Quick Commands
Execute without script file:
.nf
keypress.py "xterm" -c "ls -la" -c "pwd" -w xterm
keypress.py "leafpad" -c "Hello" -c "<Ctrl+s>" -w leafpad -n
.fi

.SS Debug Keyboard Layout
See what characters are detected:
.nf
keypress.py "leafpad" test.txt --debug
.fi

.SH MODES
.SS Normal Mode (Default)
Queries X11 keyboard mapping and respects your system layout (Finnish, German, Swedish, etc.). Properly handles AltGr symbols in extended keymap columns. Use for normal applications like text editors, terminals, browsers.

.SS Emulator Mode (\-\-emulator\-mode)
Uses hardcoded US keyboard layout, ignoring system settings. Required for emulators (DOSBox-X, VICE, MAME) because they run DOS/games internally which expect US keyboard codes. Without this flag, symbols will be wrong in emulators.

.SH WINDOW DETECTION
The program searches for the target window in two ways:

.SS By PID (Default)
Searches for a window belonging to the launched process. Works for simple cases but may fail for complex applications.

.SS By Name Pattern (\-w)
Searches for a window whose title matches the pattern (case-insensitive, partial match). More reliable:
.nf
keypress.py "app" script.txt -w "Application Name"
.fi

Use \fBxdotool search --name ""\fR to list all windows and find the correct pattern.

.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
Error (window not found, script file missing, invalid arguments, etc.)
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.Xmodmap
User keyboard mapping file (if present)
.TP
.I /usr/share/X11/xkb/
System keyboard layout definitions
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B DISPLAY
X11 display to connect to (default: :0)
.SH BUGS
.IP \(bu 2
Only works on X11, not Wayland
.IP \(bu 2
Dead keys (compose sequences) not supported
.IP \(bu 2
Unicode characters beyond your keymap not supported
.IP \(bu 2
Multi-monitor setups untested
